benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid Request: TC01-TC05 cover successful updates with 204 responses and proper payload updates.
Non-Existing Resource: TC07 covers 404 when the invoice item does not exist.
Authorization: TC13 tests missing/invalid authentication returning 401.
Malformed Payload: TC08 ensures 400 on malformed JSON payload.
Missing Required Header: TC09 validates 400 when the X-Killbill-CreatedBy header is missing.
Empty Request Body: TC10 ensures 400 for an empty request body.
Unsupported / Extra Fields: TC11 ensures 400 for extra or unsupported fields in the payload.
Large Payload Handling: TC12 and TC21 test large payload scenarios and size handling.
System/Server Errors: TC15 covers 500 internal server error scenarios.
Timeout / Gateway Timeout: TC16 covers 504 when under heavy load or timeout conditions.
Integration / Dependent Service Unavailable: TC19 covers 503 service unavailable when a dependent service is down.
Idempotency: TC17 confirms repeated identical requests are 204 with consistent results.
Regression: TC18 ensures no data loss after update scenarios.
Edge Cases: TC22 (minimum values) and TC23 (extra URL parameters) tested.
State Variation: TC24 (database empty) and TC25 (partially populated DB) exercised.
Performance: TC20 (parallel updates) and TC21 (large payload for single item) address performance aspects.
Security: SQL Injection test TC14 results in 400/422 indicating invalid input or security violation.
gaps: Partial Update: No tests validating whether PUT enforces full replacement semantics or rejects partial payloads.
Concurrency Issues: No explicit race-condition tests for concurrent updates to the same item.
Rate Limiting: No tests addressing throttling or rate limiting behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) for PUT responses.
Invalid Data Types: No tests for incorrect data types within CustomField values.
Duplicate Submission: No explicit tests beyond idempotency concerns (e.g., how duplicates are treated).
recommendations: Add a Partial Update test to verify PUT either fully replaces or rejects partial payloads per contract.
Introduce Concurrency tests simulating simultaneous updates to the same invoice item to uncover race conditions.
Add Rate Limiting tests to verify behavior under burst traffic and proper error responses.
Add Caching validations by checking for ETag/Cache-Control headers and behavior on conditional requests.
Add tests for Invalid Data Types within CustomField values to ensure robust input validation.
Clarify and test behavior for duplicate submissions beyond idempotency guarantees, and document expected outcomes.
